# shadcn-ui Integration Guidelines

## Component Usage
- Use shadcn-ui components for all UI elements
- Components are available in `src/components/ui/`
- Each component should be imported from its respective file
- Customize components using Tailwind classes

## Component Customization
- Override default styles using Tailwind classes
- Use the `cn()` utility for conditional class names
- Maintain consistent theming across components
- Follow shadcn-ui's theming guidelines

## Best Practices
- Keep component imports minimal
- Use composition to build complex UI elements
- Maintain accessibility features
- Follow responsive design principles

## Common Components
- Use `Button` for all button elements
- Use `Card` for content containers
- Use `Input` for form fields
- Use `Dialog` for modal windows
- Use `DropdownMenu` for navigation menus

## Theme Configuration
- Customize colors in `tailwind.config.js`
- Use CSS variables for theming
- Maintain dark mode support
- Follow consistent spacing scale

# shadcn-ui Components

The UI components are located in [src/components/ui/](mdc:src/components/ui). Each component is in its own file, for example:
- [src/components/ui/button.tsx](mdc:src/components/ui/button.tsx) for buttons
- [src/components/ui/card.tsx](mdc:src/components/ui/card.tsx) for cards
- [src/components/ui/input.tsx](mdc:src/components/ui/input.tsx) for form inputs

The theme configuration is in [tailwind.config.js](mdc:tailwind.config.js), which defines the color scheme and other design tokens.

To use these components in an Astro file, import them like this:
```astro
---
import { Button } from '../components/ui/button';
---
```



